WEBVTT

00:07.090 --> 00:09.923
I'm so sick of silvering myself
all day every day.

00:10.093 --> 00:11.924
I'm pissed off all the time.

00:12.095 --> 00:13.756
This is what PMS used to feel like.

00:13.931 --> 00:17.219
Our objective is to kill the witch,
finish this one way or the other.

00:17.935 --> 00:20.267
But we're gonna finish this tonight.
Are we clear?

00:20.437 --> 00:22.928
Utterly. Can we blow up these
Wiccan dipshits already?

00:23.106 --> 00:24.721
I got a mani-pedi at 4.

00:28.612 --> 00:33.106
Vampires are outside
with automatic weapons.

00:34.117 --> 00:35.618
What idiots.

00:35.786 --> 00:37.651
Listen to me.

00:37.829 --> 00:42.163
Bill and Eric are here to blow up the place.
If we don't get out, we're all gonna die.

00:42.334 --> 00:44.871
CASEY:
I gotta get out of here.

00:45.045 --> 00:46.160
Don't you get it?

00:46.338 --> 00:48.579
This is the Hotel California, baby.

00:48.757 --> 00:53.342
You can check out any time you want,
but you can't never fucking leave. Whoo!

00:53.512 --> 00:55.969
Marnie is just....

00:56.139 --> 00:57.640
MARNIE:
Roy is wrong.

00:57.808 --> 00:59.594
This is not a prison.

00:59.768 --> 01:02.510
-You may leave at any time.
LAFAYETTE: Mm-hm.

01:06.817 --> 01:09.684
You use that against the vampires.

01:09.861 --> 01:12.068
There's the door.

01:12.656 --> 01:15.398
-Good luck.
CASEY: What, do you think this is funny?

01:15.576 --> 01:19.410
We're all gonna die because of you,
you fucking bitch.

01:20.497 --> 01:21.657
TREVOR:
Casey.

01:21.832 --> 01:23.322
[CASEY GRUNTS]

01:23.500 --> 01:25.491
Marnie?

01:26.336 --> 01:28.622
TREVOR:
Casey. Casey!

01:28.797 --> 01:31.334
No, no, no. Oh, God.

01:32.009 --> 01:35.752
[CASEY GRUNTING]

01:35.929 --> 01:38.841
TREVOR: No.
-No, Casey.

03:18.740 --> 03:20.731
[MARNIE GRUNTING]

03:27.791 --> 03:30.032
-Oh, shit.
SOOKIE: What?

03:30.210 --> 03:33.498
Marnie just puked a bitch out.

03:35.132 --> 03:36.622
MARNIE:
I told you don't leave.

03:36.800 --> 03:38.961
What do you mean, "puked her out"?

03:39.136 --> 03:42.674
I mean she came right out of her
motherfucking mouth, and I can see her.

03:42.848 --> 03:44.384
[SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

03:44.558 --> 03:47.391
-How can you see any of this?
-He's a medium. It's a gift.

03:47.561 --> 03:50.348
-Since fucking when?
-What's she doing now?

03:50.522 --> 03:53.639
LAFAYETTE:
She's dirty, dark hair.

03:54.317 --> 03:55.397
It's Antonia.

03:55.569 --> 03:58.652
You murdered an innocent,
one of our own.

03:58.822 --> 04:00.983
Evil has blossomed in you.

04:01.491 --> 04:03.152
Our time together has come to an end.

04:04.244 --> 04:05.324
Our plan.

04:05.495 --> 04:08.828
-We are so close.
-You are not who I thought you were.

04:08.999 --> 04:12.992
You will not leave me.

04:13.462 --> 04:15.748
The bitch wanna leave,
but Marnie won't let her.

04:15.922 --> 04:17.958
[MARNIE CHANTING
IN LATIN]

04:20.260 --> 04:21.841
-Oh, no.
-What?

04:22.012 --> 04:24.503
A binding spell.
Marnie's binding Antonia to herself.

04:24.681 --> 04:27.013
-What does that mean?
-Means Marnie's gone bat-shit.

04:27.184 --> 04:30.347
If she binds Antonia, we're all fucked.

04:32.522 --> 04:37.687
She's pulling the bitch toward her,
but Antonia fighting it.

04:39.196 --> 04:40.857
[ANTONIA GROANING]

04:44.409 --> 04:46.024
[SIGHS]

04:47.037 --> 04:48.277
Hmm.

04:50.373 --> 04:51.874
Marnie won.

04:53.710 --> 04:55.496
We're fucked.

04:55.670 --> 04:57.001
BILL:
Eric, watch the back.

04:58.423 --> 05:00.539
JASON:
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Stop, stop, stop.

05:00.717 --> 05:03.208
-Jason.
-Stop. Stop.

05:05.055 --> 05:08.047
You can't blow that place up.
Put that down. Sookie's in there.

05:08.225 --> 05:10.887
-I told her to stay away.
-And you expected her to listen?

05:11.061 --> 05:13.143
-Fucking Sookie.
-Fucking Sookie. Put it down.

05:13.313 --> 05:14.974
JASON:
Fucking Sookie?

05:15.148 --> 05:17.059
-Fucking Sookie?
PAM: Yeah.

05:17.400 --> 05:20.892
Fucking Sookie.
As usual, she's in the goddamn way.

05:21.071 --> 05:22.402
I don't believe this.

05:22.572 --> 05:26.406
Hey, Sookie picked you up cold and scared
off the side of the road...

05:26.576 --> 05:29.613
-...and opened her home to you.
-Well, technically, it's my home.

05:29.788 --> 05:32.746
Fuck you, chump. It's her house.

05:33.333 --> 05:36.666
And you, how many times
has Sookie saved your life?

05:37.087 --> 05:40.579
Letting you drink her blood
like it was your own private soda fountain.

05:40.924 --> 05:44.758
And now you'd even think about hurting her
just to settle some score.

05:46.304 --> 05:49.262
Are you both fucking nuts?

05:52.102 --> 05:53.137
We must abort.

05:54.771 --> 05:55.806
I agree.

05:56.189 --> 05:57.690
PAM:
Holy shit, gentlemen.

05:57.858 --> 06:02.101
Do not tell me you'd put our entire species
at risk for a gash in a sundress.

06:04.447 --> 06:06.108
We have to find another way.

06:07.409 --> 06:11.618
And just so you know,
Marnie put a spell on the whole place.

06:11.788 --> 06:13.449
Watch this.

06:17.961 --> 06:19.826
Goes around the whole dang place.

06:22.883 --> 06:24.714
We have to disable it.

06:24.885 --> 06:26.591
Damn straight.

06:30.473 --> 06:32.634
Why are you staring daggers at me?

06:32.809 --> 06:34.310
Wasn't even looking at you.

06:34.477 --> 06:36.183
Yeah, you were.

06:37.480 --> 06:40.643
And I still feel guilty, okay? So sue me.

06:40.817 --> 06:42.773
Jason, I don't care how you feel.

06:44.529 --> 06:47.236
You're the furthest thing
from my mind, okay?

06:48.700 --> 06:50.236
Good.

06:51.328 --> 06:54.820
ERIC: We gotta think about Sookie.
BILL: Well, then we can't use explosives.

06:55.498 --> 06:56.487
JASON:
Look out.

06:58.251 --> 06:59.627
Stalling time's over.

07:00.670 --> 07:02.501
Where the hell is he?

07:02.672 --> 07:05.209
That gun's not exactly
helping my memory.

07:05.383 --> 07:06.919
Sam.

07:11.348 --> 07:14.055
-Where's Marcus?
-New Mexico.

07:14.225 --> 07:16.181
-New Mexico?
-Yeah.

07:16.353 --> 07:17.718
Oh, no. Hold on.

07:17.896 --> 07:19.352
No, no, he's in Brazil.

07:19.522 --> 07:20.682
Fucking asshole.

07:20.857 --> 07:22.848
Oh, shoot. My bad.

07:23.026 --> 07:24.766
He's in fucking Disneyland.

07:24.945 --> 07:26.560
[ALL GRUNT]

07:26.738 --> 07:29.480
-Where is he?
-Hey, new guy.

07:29.658 --> 07:32.274
I don't know how they did things
down in Mississippi...

07:32.452 --> 07:35.910
...but in Shreveport, we don't sell out
our packmaster to no shifter.

07:36.081 --> 07:38.037
Your packmaster's a sociopath.

07:38.208 --> 07:41.291
Made us accessories to murder.
That someone you want to protect?

07:41.461 --> 07:42.667
LUNA:
Marcus? Emma?

07:43.588 --> 07:44.998
SAM:
Luna?

07:45.173 --> 07:47.038
Where is Marcus? I'm gonna kill him.

07:47.217 --> 07:50.004
Emma's missing.
Son of a bitch snatched her out of school.

07:50.178 --> 07:52.760
Tell me where he is
or I will fucking kill you!

07:52.931 --> 07:54.137
-Tell me where.
-Easy.

07:54.307 --> 07:57.390
-Fucking tell me where he is!
-Easy. Easy now. Easy.

07:57.560 --> 07:59.721
Hey, hey, hey.

07:59.896 --> 08:02.763
-Hey, we'll find Emma.
-Why are you here?

08:04.192 --> 08:05.728
Marcus murdered my brother.

08:06.903 --> 08:08.109
He did what? Oh, my God.

08:08.279 --> 08:13.364
Listen.
I need to find him and set things right.

08:13.535 --> 08:15.071
This isn't a wolf-shifter thing.

08:15.578 --> 08:19.287
It's right and wrong, plain and simple.

08:19.457 --> 08:22.620
Now, unless you wanna be accomplice
to kidnapping too...

08:23.211 --> 08:24.747
...you tell me where Marcus went.

08:29.968 --> 08:32.755
NATE:
He said he'd be back. That's all I know.

08:32.929 --> 08:35.796
-Debbie, just listen to me.
-l'm listening, Marcus.

08:35.974 --> 08:37.635
You're not listening.

08:37.809 --> 08:39.549
I ain't going away with you.

08:39.728 --> 08:42.094
-I can't.
-Daddy?

08:42.731 --> 08:46.269
-You mean you won't.
-Right. I won't.

08:46.776 --> 08:48.767
I like you.

08:49.279 --> 08:51.270
-I really do.
-Daddy.

08:51.781 --> 08:54.272
-What, sweetie?
-I wanna talk to Mommy.

08:56.953 --> 08:58.614
Look.

09:00.874 --> 09:03.160
Your mommy's busy right now, Emma.

09:03.334 --> 09:06.201
Why don't you go color, huh?

09:06.379 --> 09:08.791
Let your daddy talk to his friend
for a minute, okay?

09:08.965 --> 09:11.877
-Okay.
-All right.

09:12.969 --> 09:14.709
[SIGHS]

09:18.850 --> 09:23.640
Look, you and me,
we make sense together.

09:23.813 --> 09:26.145
And I promise you this:

09:27.817 --> 09:29.478
I'll get you off the V.

09:30.528 --> 09:31.904
Is that right?

09:32.072 --> 09:33.608
[DEBBIE SCOFFS]

09:34.991 --> 09:37.357
You know, I've tried, Marcus.

09:37.827 --> 09:39.533
I'm trying.

09:39.704 --> 09:41.569
It ain't easy.

09:44.501 --> 09:48.369
That's because Alcide ain't giving you
the one thing you really need...

09:48.546 --> 09:51.128
...and you turn to that V shit
to feel whole.

09:51.299 --> 09:53.381
Alcide loves me.
He gives me plenty of love.

09:53.551 --> 09:57.339
I ain't talking about love.
I'm talking about children.

09:57.931 --> 10:00.718
He ain't ever gonna step up to that plate.

10:01.226 --> 10:03.592
Emma, she needs a mom.

10:03.770 --> 10:06.557
Ain't talking about a shifter mom, neither.

10:06.731 --> 10:09.689
I mean a real mom. A Were.

10:14.531 --> 10:16.522
| just can't.

10:17.242 --> 10:19.028
Why not?

10:20.370 --> 10:22.361
Because I love Alcide.

10:22.872 --> 10:24.533
I'm sorry.

10:25.542 --> 10:29.205
-Then why you with me?
-Alcide ain't been faithful.

10:29.754 --> 10:31.710
I told you that.

10:33.216 --> 10:35.047
I don't buy it.

10:35.552 --> 10:37.884
l ain'tjust a revenge fuck to you.

10:43.226 --> 10:45.888
I can't stick around here.

10:47.981 --> 10:52.896
Why don't we just pack a bag,
grab Emma and get out of here?

10:57.282 --> 10:59.068
Oh, my God.

11:00.118 --> 11:02.074
-She's got a pulse.
TREVOR: She's alive?

11:02.245 --> 11:03.906
-What?
-You want me to shoot her?

11:04.080 --> 11:05.320
No.

11:05.498 --> 11:06.578
She does?

11:08.001 --> 11:09.491
You see?

11:10.753 --> 11:12.084
I'm no murderer.

11:12.255 --> 11:15.292
Yeah, you're a regular fucking
humanitarian.

11:15.466 --> 11:17.457
JESUS:
It's barely there.

11:18.178 --> 11:20.089
Marnie, please.

11:20.763 --> 11:22.424
Please, let me try to save her.

11:23.433 --> 11:26.800
Well, yes. I mean, you're a nurse.
Of course.

11:27.979 --> 11:33.940
Okay. We're gonna need, uh, hot water
and towels to stanch the bleeding.

11:34.110 --> 11:35.611
Help me get her to the bathroom.

11:35.778 --> 11:36.858
-l'll help.
JESUS: No.

11:37.030 --> 11:40.363
No, I need someone
who won't be emotional.

11:40.533 --> 11:43.366
Come on. Now, goddamn it.

11:43.536 --> 11:45.072
[ALL MURMURING]

11:51.127 --> 11:52.458
JESUS:
Right here.

11:58.843 --> 12:00.424
She looks so stiff.

12:08.645 --> 12:11.762
-Boyfriend, she's dead.
-I know.

12:11.940 --> 12:14.477
-You said she had a pulse.
-We need to force Antonia...

12:14.651 --> 12:18.143
...out of Marnie's body before she kills us.
We need Casey's body to do that.

12:18.321 --> 12:19.356
Force Antonia out?

12:19.530 --> 12:22.863
How the fuck we gonna do that?
With a damn ghost crowbar?

12:23.034 --> 12:26.572
Sort of.
It's brujo shit and it's gonna be ugly.

12:26.746 --> 12:29.658
Look, I need to go get some things.

12:29.832 --> 12:31.493
Don't go anywhere, okay?

12:32.001 --> 12:33.502
Well, that'll be fucking easy.

12:39.008 --> 12:39.997
I need a few things...

12:40.176 --> 12:43.009
-...for disinfecting and cauterizing.
-Use anything you need.

13:00.196 --> 13:03.188
|-- I am terribly sorry about Casey.

13:04.784 --> 13:07.275
It was self-defense.

13:07.996 --> 13:10.533
Marnie, it was almost murder.

13:13.042 --> 13:17.206
I've known you for years.
You're one of the gentlest people I know.

13:17.380 --> 13:18.836
Why would you do such a thing?

13:19.007 --> 13:22.966
She was about to jeopardize everything
we've worked for, Holly.

13:23.136 --> 13:25.969
I don't know you very well,
but from everything I've heard...

13:26.139 --> 13:30.257
...you've always been such a kind,
loving person.

13:30.435 --> 13:31.891
I was a doormat.

13:32.770 --> 13:36.012
All my life,
I've lived in fear of other people.

13:36.899 --> 13:39.185
And now for once,
people are frightened of me.

13:39.360 --> 13:40.736
And that's a good thing?

13:40.903 --> 13:42.643
Well, yes, I prefer it.

13:43.406 --> 13:45.567
You've been to my house
for Thanksgiving.

13:45.742 --> 13:47.573
You've played with my kids.

13:47.744 --> 13:51.111
I don't believe you'd hurt me
just because I don't agree with you.

13:51.289 --> 13:53.245
Don't patronize me.

13:53.416 --> 13:55.407
And don't coddle me like a child.

13:57.587 --> 14:00.875
I don't want to hurt anyone.

14:01.049 --> 14:04.962
-But Casey was--
-Casey attacked me.

14:05.136 --> 14:09.721
I had every right.
I am not a punching bag.

14:09.891 --> 14:11.131
I get it.

14:11.309 --> 14:13.470
You've always felt like an outsider...

14:13.644 --> 14:17.228
...and now you feel like people
are finally respecting you.

14:17.398 --> 14:20.265
Well, yes. That's right.

14:20.443 --> 14:23.651
I understand.
Sometimes I feel like a freak too.

14:23.821 --> 14:26.984
-I'm not a freak.
-| just meant I feel misunderstood.

14:27.158 --> 14:30.491
Sometimes picked on, even.

14:30.661 --> 14:32.492
You just want connection.

14:33.289 --> 14:35.325
HOLLY:
And you got it.

14:35.500 --> 14:38.458
We're all on your side.

14:38.628 --> 14:40.459
We're your friends.

14:40.630 --> 14:42.336
SOOKIE:
Please.

14:42.507 --> 14:44.964
Marnie, you can end this.

14:46.969 --> 14:49.802
You have all the power.

14:49.972 --> 14:51.963
[SIGHS]

14:54.143 --> 14:56.225
Ah. What kind of Christian...?

14:56.396 --> 14:59.513
I mean, what kind of man
just up and deserts his cousin...

14:59.690 --> 15:01.976
...in the middle of the goddamn woods?

15:02.151 --> 15:06.315
Fucking PTSD'd-out degenerate,
that's who.

15:06.489 --> 15:08.821
I swear to holy Jesus, Terry Bellefleur...

15:08.991 --> 15:12.358
...I will punch your face to the back
of your head when I get home.

15:13.663 --> 15:15.324
You mean if you get home.

15:15.498 --> 15:19.036
Oh, now don't start with that negative talk.
It's not helpful.

15:19.210 --> 15:21.826
Screw helpful, moron.
We're in dire fucking straights.

15:22.004 --> 15:26.338
Well, do you think I don't know that?
Who the fuck am I talking to?

15:26.509 --> 15:29.342
Shep, hold it together, man.

15:29.846 --> 15:32.508
Don't go all Iost—in-nature retarded.

15:32.682 --> 15:35.640
[ENERGY PULSATING]

15:44.360 --> 15:46.191
Holy God.

15:46.529 --> 15:48.895
-Stay away.
-Ma'am, I'm not gonna hurt you.

15:49.073 --> 15:50.153
[SNIFFS]

15:50.324 --> 15:51.700
Stay back.

15:51.868 --> 15:54.029
Ma'am, I'm a police officer.

15:54.704 --> 15:56.660
[ANDY GRUNTS]

16:02.295 --> 16:04.911
They're probably in another state
by now.

16:05.089 --> 16:07.796
Mexico's only a few hundred miles away.

16:07.967 --> 16:09.503
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

16:11.262 --> 16:14.800
Hello? Emma.
Oh, my God. Are you okay?

16:15.558 --> 16:17.264
Honey, are you with Daddy?

16:18.394 --> 16:21.227
Where are you?
She doesn't know where she is.

16:21.397 --> 16:24.059
-Just check the phone number.
-Baby, hold on.

16:24.484 --> 16:25.940
That's my number.

16:26.402 --> 16:28.188
She's in my house?

16:31.407 --> 16:32.817
Do you see?

16:32.992 --> 16:35.734
Do you see what awaits you
if you walk with Antonia?

16:36.078 --> 16:37.579
ERIC:
Don't bother.

16:38.247 --> 16:40.454
That witch had complete control
over me.

16:41.584 --> 16:44.246
She's a robot. She must die.

16:44.420 --> 16:45.580
[BILL GROWLS]

16:45.755 --> 16:47.086
Wait.

16:49.800 --> 16:51.791
Vintage Cartier.

16:52.512 --> 16:54.924
I'll take good care of this.

16:55.348 --> 16:57.259
Sorry. Go ahead.

16:58.976 --> 17:01.763
Is there no way that she can be saved,
as you were?

17:02.271 --> 17:03.602
Well, it's possible, but I--

17:03.773 --> 17:06.105
KIRSCH:
It's you who needs saving.

17:06.275 --> 17:09.142
I serve Antonia Gavilan de Logroﬁo.

17:09.946 --> 17:12.858
You will all walk in the sun
and roast like pigs.

17:13.032 --> 17:14.943
[LAUGHS]

17:15.159 --> 17:16.820
[KIRSCH SCREAMS]

17:18.246 --> 17:19.827
Antonia.

17:21.290 --> 17:22.791
Show your face, witch.

17:22.959 --> 17:27.293
Hiding behind magic like a coward
does not become you.

17:29.465 --> 17:30.875
You were right.

17:32.802 --> 17:35.965
It's time for negotiation.

17:43.020 --> 17:44.681
The vampires seem to like you.

17:46.482 --> 17:47.471
Will you join me?

17:50.570 --> 17:52.401
Bill. Eric.

17:53.406 --> 17:54.987
Marnie wants to negotiate.

17:55.366 --> 17:57.482
How may I serve Antonia?

17:57.660 --> 17:58.740
Be quiet.

17:58.911 --> 18:00.492
[CHANTS IN LATIN]

18:05.793 --> 18:07.203
Oh, my God.

18:07.378 --> 18:09.585
[KIRSCH SCREAMING]

18:21.726 --> 18:25.844
Amazing, isn't it?
The power of the sun harnessed.

18:26.188 --> 18:29.851
The protection spell is impenetrable
to most humans, and not fatal.

18:30.026 --> 18:35.692
But to vampires, one touch,
death sentence.

18:38.534 --> 18:41.367
BILL: It makes no difference
what you hide behind.

18:41.537 --> 18:43.368
You have killed your last vampire.

18:43.539 --> 18:45.040
How optimistic.

18:45.207 --> 18:46.663
Let the girl go.

18:46.834 --> 18:49.371
Oh, so you'd like to negotiate?

18:49.545 --> 18:50.955
Let the girl go.

18:52.256 --> 18:55.419
Fine. The girl can go.

18:56.385 --> 18:58.671
But I'll need something in exchange.

18:58.846 --> 19:00.962
-What?
-Anything.

19:02.642 --> 19:03.927
Your lives.

19:05.478 --> 19:08.094
Kill yourselves and she walks free.

19:10.024 --> 19:11.764
Both of you.

19:12.610 --> 19:14.441
-Good one.
-Don't laugh too much.

19:14.612 --> 19:16.728
You wouldn't want your lips to fall off.

19:16.906 --> 19:20.319
Come on. Just make them a real offer.
They'll listen. I know them. They--

19:20.493 --> 19:21.903
Iaccept

19:22.078 --> 19:23.238
-Fine.
BOTH: What?

19:23.412 --> 19:26.245
-No.No.
-Quiet.

19:27.958 --> 19:30.620
I have your word?
You will set her free?

19:31.253 --> 19:34.586
Free as a resurrected bird.

